Description: Plastic box (with yellow label '41') with transparent lid containing small fragments of papyrus. A label reads '3 layers papyrus fragments. (Various + cartonnage)'. A label by Stephen Quirke reads 'Late Period hieratic BD with black vigns, two pieces; Late Period hypocephalus; Late Period hierogls (small), 3 fragments; two corners of (Late Period vign.) frame; Greek; cartonnage figured pieces. Stored Students [Room] JAN 1992'. The fragments inside are unmounted and unglazed.
Curator's comments: Previously unregistered material stored in Papyrus Store.
